cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with pedestrian detection using deep learning methods applied to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of convolutional networks and sparse coding also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the evaluation of results on various datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
